===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|leven|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|sc=Latinx|lǣfan||to leave}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*laibijaną||to let stay, leave}}, causative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*lībaną||to stay, remain}}. Cognate with {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|lēva||to leave|lang=ofs}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term/t|osx|lēvian}}, {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|leiban||to leave|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|leifa||leave over|lang=non}} (whence Icelandic {{term|leifa|lang=is}}), {{term|lifna||to be left|lang=non}} (whence Danish {{term|levne|lang=da}}). More at [[lave#Etymology_2|lave]], [[belive#Etymology_1|belive]].

